ntence. Even better, use a label."), mdx("h3", null, "Check Contrast"), mdx("p", null, "Make sure the contrast ratios of text on backgrounds are meeting accessibility standards. Contrast ratios should be at least 3:1 for large text and 4.5:1 for small text. "), mdx("p", null, "I use a Figma plugin called Contrast to quickly check contrast ratios in my designs.  "), mdx("h3", null, "Use Established Patterns"), mdx("p", null, "People use and are familiar with many UIs. Piggyback on their prior knowledge to make your UI easier to understand and use. Don\u2019t ask users to learn novel layouts and interactions if it\u2019s not necessary. "), mdx("p", null, "Examples of established patterns include:"), mdx("ul", null, mdx("li", {
