ct from one another. "), mdx("h3", null, "Consolidate Styles and Apply Them Consistently"), mdx("p", null, "Don\u2019t use three styles when one style will do.  "), mdx("p", null, "Styles should support levels of hierarchy in the UI (e.g. headings and paragraphs, primary and secondary actions). Remove styles that aren\u2019t serving this purpose. Add styles only to fill gaps in hierarchy. Then apply them consistently across the UI."), mdx("p", null, "This goes for text and interactive elements. "), mdx("h2", null, "Wrapping Up"), mdx("p", null, "The six fundamentals listed above summarize technical knowledge and best practices that make it easier for humans to interact with software on screens. "), mdx("p", null, "Taken together, they can quickly transform a UI from confusing, frustrating, and inefficient to something that\u2019s clear, accessible, and usable. "));
